title: Another empty trip
text:
John Minchillo 'Cat scratched 
UCon quarterback Bryant Shirreffs, center, is tackled by Cincinnati defensive end Kimoni Fitz, left, and linebacker Kevin Brown during the second half of Cincinnati's 37-13 victory Saturday. (AP Photo/John Minchillo) Posted: Saturday, October 24, 2015 10:21 pm Journal Inquirer Journal Inquirer | 0 comments 
CINCINNATI -- The University of Connecticut football team remains 0-for-Nippert Stadium. And like most of the Huskies' previous forays onto the University of Cincinnati campus, this one wasn’t very competitive. 
Cincinnati quarterback Gunner Kiel returned from an injury to throw for 327 yards as the Bearcats pounded UConn 37-13 Saturday evening before a record crowd of 40,124 at the newly refurbished Nippert Stadium. 
The Huskies (3-5, 1-3 American Athletic Conference) have lost five of their last six games after an encouraging hot start.
